<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-28T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-28T20:00:00-05:00" n="45" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3–147: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Butterworth</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-01T09:00:00+08:00">March 1,
                                    1947—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received February 28—9:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>403. I am confidentially and reliably informed that T. V. Soong<note n="83" xml:id="d45fn1">President of the Chinese Executive
                                Yuan.</note> offered his resignation to the Generalissimo<note n="84" xml:id="d45fn2">Chiang Kai-shek, President of the National
                                Government of the Republic of China.</note> last evening and the
                            latter accepted.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Butterworth</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>